  ‚ôę Ore of Diamond ‚ôę
#- ‚ôę With our picks and gear we're fairin' 
 On the wild and wasteful caverns,
 It's down there in the deep, we harvest, and reap our bread.
 
As we hunt, the shiny
ore, -- of diamond ‚ôę


           -Śćź-           
#- ‚ôę Oh, it was a fine and a pleasant day, out of Volkstag mines, I was faring', As a cabin boy and a mining lover. For to hunt the shiny ore of diamond... 

Oh, we left the home grounds in the month of june... ‚ôę

           -Śćź-
#- ‚ôę And those channy sheild, we sure were wearin' with a hundred prots and the silk touch pickaxe. That we takin' from ---
the ore of diamond..

 Now the work was hard, and the hours long... ‚ôę

           -Śćź-
#- ‚ôę And the treatment' sure, it took some bearin', 

 And i used to sleep, standing on my feet,

 As I dreamed about,
 the ore of diamond ‚ôę



           -Śćź-
#- ‚ôę Now, you're down below, you're a mining man, and ya learnin' bout mine fairin'

 That's ye education, with scraps of--
navigation, As you hunt the shiny ore--
of diamond ‚ôę


           -Śćź-
#- ‚ôę In the gloomy deep,
and the livin' holes,--
Just to earn your daily bread, youre darin' From the riechstag tower to,--
the volkstag islands,
 You're following--
the ore of diamond ‚ôę



           -Śćź-
#- ‚ôę Well, I earned my keep and i payed my way, And i earned the gear, i was wearin'
 Mine one million miles,
mine ten million iron,
  
 We were mining for the ore of diamond ‚ôę



           -Śćź-
#- ‚ôę And it's night and day, we're mining...
 Come winds or waves of griefer gales, sweating off the cold,

growing up...
growing old....
or dying,-- ‚ôę



           -Śćź-
#- ‚ôę As we hunt,--

 the shiny ore,--

 of diamond. ‚ôę







